Austroargiolestes chrysoides is a species of Australian damselfly in the family Megapodagrionidae,
commonly known as a golden flatwing. 
It is endemic to south-eastern Queensland, where it inhabits streams in rainforest.Austroargiolestes chrysoides is a medium-sized to large, black and yellow damselfly, without pruinescence.
Like other members of the family Megapodagrionidae. it rests with its wings outspread.